description: Measure the voltage directly at the switched output terminals of the control module (the two wires going to the load module) during a lamp shut-off event to determine if the relay is in fact opening or if supply to the load is being maintained. This will clarify if the interruption is due to the relay or if the issue lies downstream (in the load module or its diode/load wiring)., outcome="Voltage at 'Control Output Cable (+)' is 0.3592 V, and at 'Control Output Cable (−)' is 0.0003 V during the lamp shut-off event. This indicates there is a low voltage present at the switched output terminals while the relay is expected to be open. No polarity inversion is detected in the measured voltages.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Load module (across the diode and lamp connections),
description: Measure the voltage directly across the diode and both lamps in the load module during the lamp shut-off event to determine if the low output voltage from the control module is reaching the load and which portion of the load circuit is dropping the voltage. This will help isolate if the diode or the lamps are causing the periodic shut-off., outcome='Voltage measurements show 0.3592 V at the anode and 0.0003 V at the cathode of the load protection diode. Both the main load lamp and the internal indicator lamp have 0.0003 V across both terminals. The low voltage reading at the diode cathode and both lamps indicates that minimal voltage is reaching past the diode, suggesting the primary voltage drop occurs at the diode.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=65.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Power supply module battery,
description: Test the voltage across the battery terminals during a lamp shut-off event to check for intermittent voltage drops that could cause the control module output voltage to sag below relay holding thresholds., outcome='Measured voltage at the battery terminals is 12.0 V on the positive terminal and 0.0 V on the negative terminal with respect to ground during the lamp shut-off event. No unexpected voltage drop across the battery was detected at this time.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=30.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control module relay output contacts,
description: Test the continuity (resistance) directly across the relay output contacts in the control module during a lamp shut-off event. This will confirm if the relay contacts are truly opening (high resistance) or if there is some high-resistance connection or bad solder joint causing voltage drop when they should be closed., outcome="Continuity test across the 'Control Relay' contacts shows nominal resistance (0.01 Ω), which matches the expected value. The relay contacts are making good electrical connection with no indication of a high-resistance path or bad solder joint.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=25.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
